                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290115-208-off1112 t18290115-208-crimeloc1115"></join>. On the 13th of January, between ten and eleven o'clock in the evening, I was in the parlour, and heard a pair of scales rattle, which were on the sugar; I looked, and saw the prisoner - he was just leaving the door, with something which I thought was a loaf of sugar; I followed him, and he dropped the sugar - I never lost sight of him till he was stopped at the corner, eight doors off; I saw the sugar again in three or four minutes.</p>
               <p>
            
